Divine Omens and Patronage

The divine omen system tracks the influence of Mitra, Gaea, and Set across the
world. Player action can push pressure toward a god. If one god has enough
pressure, and enough distance from the others, that god becomes ascendant.

If no god clears that threshold, the world is Godless. Personal patron ranks
still work during Godless periods, but ascendance bonuses and Set's ascendant
pressure do not.

Useful commands:

  omens                         Read the current world omen.
  portents                      Alias for omens.
  patron                        Read your personal patronage.
  patron gods                   Learn the three patron identities.
  patron pledge <mitra|gaea|set> Pledge yourself to a patron.
  patron renounce               Break your current pledge.
  patron favor                  Read your broad favor standing.
  patron pilgrimage start       Begin a shrine pilgrimage.
  patron pilgrimage status      Check your active pilgrimage.
  tithe <amount> to <god>       Offer coins toward a god's pressure.
  tithe <amount> at shrine      Tithe at the shrine in your room.
  pray at shrine                Pray at the shrine in your room.
  meter                         Check Wrathful Avatar charge and rate.
  score                         Check Wrathful Avatar charge and rate.

Shrines, tithes, pilgrimages, Holy Hours, marked enemies, and rare events all
feed into the divine cycle.

Shrines can currently be found at:

  Mitra  The Temple of Mitra in DarkWind City.
  Gaea   The rose garden near the chapel.
  Set    The black altar in the temple of Qazaash.

Patron ranks and world omens affect Wrathful Avatar charge. The system hides
raw favor and pressure numbers on purpose; the public commands describe broad
standing, current omens, and visible divine events without exposing exact
tables.

